Description: I bought this guitar when I was looking for my musical "style", but I enjoy writing more acoustic folky songs, so this one is rarely ever touched and has spent most of its life inside its case. I'll be moving to Thailand soon and am letting go of my bigger ticket items to fund my travels, I'd love to see it go to a good new home where it will finally get some proper play time. This is a great guitar for any intermediate/experienced player (perfect for the holidays) and truly looks like a piece of art. I paid $2500 for it new, asking only half of that now :). Comes in the original Taylor Alligator Leather Case. Description:The T5 Standard features a Sitka Spruce top paired with hollow sapele body, yielding a blend of acoustic resonance and electric horsepower. The electric/acoustic hybrid incorporates a three-pickup configuration: an acoustic body sensor, a concealed neck humbucker, and a visible bridge humbucker. Run the T5 through an acoustic and electric amp and work the five-way switch to fully experience the guitar's tonal range. Please Note:*The leather case has a couple minor paint spots on the outside. They are white and the biggest is about the size of a quarter. (They can easily be covered up with a sticker if desired).*I have removed the strings for cleaning and safer shipping. Guitar will ship inside of its case, which is packaged inside of a larger box filled with cushioning. Happy Hunting!
